         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we establish error bounds for a finite-difference approximation to solutions of certain parabolic systems of the form $v_t + f(v)_x = \varepsilon v_{xx}$. We assume that the Cauchy data is of class BV, and we show that the sup norm of the error is bounded by $O(\Delta x|\ln \Delta x|)$ at positive times.</p>
          </abstract>
